{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "388eca23-3a31-4bc4-bb0f-2210a264dcfa",
    "name": "ollama-mcp-server (MCP / JSON-RPC tests)",
    "description": "Automated tests for the ollama-mcp-server MCP endpoint, driven over the Streamable HTTP transport (POST {{baseUrl}}/mcp) using JSON-RPC 2.0.\n\nUNLIKE Postman's interactive 'MCP Request' panel, this is a regular Collection so it runs `pm.test` assertions in the Collection Runner / Newman.\n\nRun the requests IN ORDER (the Runner does this top-down): initialize captures the Mcp-Session-Id that every later request needs.\n\nRequests 1-3 (initialize, notifications/initialized, tools/list) need only the MCP server. Requests 4-5 (ollama_*) need the remote Ollama host. Request 7 (run_postman_collection) shells out to Newman and needs the API that the server's default collection targets to be running; it is skipped gracefully (logs a note) if Newman or that API is unavailable.\n\nVariables:\n- baseUrl: where the server listens (default http://localhost:8085)\n- model: model used by ollama_generate (default qwen3:8b — small/fast)\n- sessionId / protocolVersion: filled in automatically by the initialize request.\n\nEach test inlines a tiny mcpResult() helper that returns the parsed JSON-RPC envelope whether the server replied with application/json or an SSE 'data:' frame.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "4991288"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. initialize",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "function mcpResult(){var b=pm.response.text().replace(/^\\uFEFF/,'').trim();if(b.charAt(0)!=='{'&&b.indexOf('data:')!==-1){b=b.split(/\\r?\\n/).filter(function(l){return l.indexOf('data:')===0;}).map(function(l){return l.slice(5).trim();}).join('');}return JSON.parse(b);}",
              "",
              "// MCP handshake step 1. Capture the session id (required on every later request).",
              "pm.test('initialize returns 200', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
              "",
              "var sid = pm.response.headers.get('Mcp-Session-Id');",
              "pm.test('server issued an Mcp-Session-Id', function () { pm.expect(sid).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty; });",
              "if (sid) { pm.collectionVariables.set('sessionId', sid); }",
              "",
              "var rpc = mcpResult();",
              "if (rpc.result && rpc.result.protocolVersion) { pm.collectionVariables.set('protocolVersion', rpc.result.protocolVersion); }",
              "pm.test('serverInfo.name is ollama-mcp-server', function () {",
              "  pm.expect(rpc.result.serverInfo.name).to.eql('ollama-mcp-server');",
              "});"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "packages": {},
            "requests": {}
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          },
          {
            "key": "Accept",
            "value": "application/json, text/event-stream"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n    \"id\": 1,\n    \"method\": \"initialize\",\n    \"params\": {\n        \"protocolVersion\": \"{{protocolVersion}}\",\n        \"capabilities\": {},\n        \"clientInfo\": {\n            \"name\": \"postman-collection\",\n            \"version\": \"1.0.0\"\n        }\n    }\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/mcp",
          "host": [
            "{{baseUrl}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "mcp"
          ]
        }
      },
      "response": []
    },
